      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TAW MAJOR (2) is a progressive type who recorded his 11th career win last time out (29.56) at this track. Has a good record here at this journey. Winner at his latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. Ideally placed to take this out. MUSTANG ETHICS (1) filled a minor placing last start at Maitland behind Zipping Hagen (25.46) in a Grade 4/5. Chased the leaders and with a clean run can be prominent. Ran one of the fastest times on the program last start despite finishing in the minors. Hard to beat again. ZIPPING ARIEL (7) shapes well after a decent run last time, finishing third in a NG at Richmond in 29.64. This is tougher but looks a leading chance again. PAX BOSTONIA (5) has a solid strike rate at this distance.",
